<section id="field-states" class="method-section" tabindex="-1"><p class="section-number">01</p><div><p class="eyebrow">How to read certainty</p><h2>The Data Changes Material</h2><div class="state-manual">
  <article class="manual-high"><span>VERIFIED FORECAST</span><h3>Time-matched outlook</h3><p>A named, non-degraded forecast includes both its forecast-valid time and fetch time, and both lineups are confirmed.</p></article>
  <article class="manual-high"><span>OBSERVED</span><h3>Measured snapshot</h3><p>A sourced observation includes its observation time and both lineups are confirmed. This label is never used for forecast data.</p></article>
  <article class="manual-medium"><span>PROJECTED</span><h3>Lineup still forming</h3><p>The weather receipt is verified, but at least one lineup is not confirmed. The weather vectors remain usable without overstating lineup certainty.</p></article>
  <article class="manual-low"><span>SOURCE UNVERIFIED</span><h3>Weather withheld</h3><p>A model row exists, but its weather source, degradation flag, or required time receipt is incomplete. The schedule and published factor remain visible while weather vectors stay hidden.</p></article>
  <article class="manual-low"><span>INCOMPLETE</span><h3>De-inked instrument</h3><p>A required input is missing. The interface hatches the number instead of silently inserting neutral weather.</p></article>
  <article class="manual-suspended"><span>ROOF</span><h3>Physics suspended</h3><p>Outdoor wind is intentionally becalmed for a closed or controlled venue.</p></article>
</div></div></section>

<section id="worked-example" class="method-section" tabindex="-1"><p class="section-number">02</p><div><p class="eyebrow">Live payload example</p><h2>One Factor, Fully Decomposed</h2>
  {#if example && example.daily_pf_runs != null}
    <div class="equation"><span><small>{example.venue}</small>{factor(example.seasonal_pf_runs)}</span><i>×</i><span><small>game-time conditions</small>{example.seasonal_pf_runs ? factor(example.daily_pf_runs / example.seasonal_pf_runs) : '—'}</span><i>=</i><span><small>Game-time scoring factor</small>{factor(example.daily_pf_runs)}</span></div>
    <p>The result is <strong class="mono">{movementLabel(example)}</strong>. This is a factor ratio—not a count of expected runs.</p>
  {:else}<p>No complete game exists in the loaded slate, so this worked example is withheld.</p>{/if}
</div></section>

<section id="approaches" class="method-section" tabindex="-1"><p class="section-number">03</p><div><p class="eyebrow">Model lineage</p><h2>From Proxy to Physics</h2><div class="approach-grid"><article><span>APPROACH B</span><h3>Weather-conditioned empirical fit</h3><p>Historical outcomes estimate how a park responds under similar air. Useful, but bounded by the examples the record already contains.</p></article><article><span>APPROACH C</span><h3>Trajectory-informed adjustment</h3><p>Flight physics transforms carry and cross-wind components before reconnecting them to venue geometry. Simulation labels stay visible until validated.</p></article></div></div></section>

<section id="sources" class="method-section" tabindex="-1"><p class="section-number">04</p><div><p class="eyebrow">Inputs and cadence</p><h2>Station Log</h2><div class="source-table" role="table" aria-label="Data source cadence"><div role="row"><span role="columnheader">INPUT</span><span role="columnheader">CADENCE</span><span role="columnheader">DEGRADED BEHAVIOR</span></div><div role="row"><span role="cell">MLB schedule / venue</span><span role="cell">slate refresh</span><span role="cell">game omitted only if identity is unsafe</span></div><div role="row"><span role="cell">Game-hour weather forecast</span><span role="cell">each slate refresh</span><span role="cell">vectors withheld when source, valid time, or fetch time is incomplete</span></div><div role="row"><span role="cell">Weather observation</span><span role="cell">when explicitly published</span><span role="cell">never inferred from forecast data</span></div><div role="row"><span role="cell">Lineups</span><span role="cell">as posted</span><span role="cell">PROJECTED material state</span></div><div role="row"><span role="cell">Outcome grading</span><span role="cell">verified close</span><span role="cell">current-slate evidence remains available</span></div></div></div></section>

<section id="glossary" class="method-section" tabindex="-1"><p class="section-number">05</p><div><p class="eyebrow">Plain-language glossary</p><h2>Every Term, In Plain English</h2><dl class="glossary">
  <div><dt>Run Scoring Factor</dt><dd>The model’s projected scoring environment relative to MLB average. A factor of 1.12 is 12% above average; 0.93 is 7% below average. It is not a literal run count.</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Home Run Factor</dt><dd>The same idea, for home runs specifically. Above 1.00 favors hitters, below 1.00 favors pitchers.</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Factor movement vs baseline</dt><dd>The percentage ratio between the game-time scoring factor and this park’s baseline. +12% means the model moved the factor 12% above the park comparison point—not that it added 0.12 or 12 runs.</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Wind Carry</dt><dd>The net wind component along the ball's flight, in mph. Positive carries the ball toward the outfield (helps hitters); negative holds it in.</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Air density</dt><dd>How thin or heavy tonight's air is. Thin air — heat, altitude, low humidity — lets a batted ball travel farther.</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Instrument states</dt><dd><strong>Verified forecast</strong>: sourced, non-degraded forecast with valid and fetch times plus confirmed lineups. <strong>Observed</strong>: sourced observation with an observation time plus confirmed lineups. <strong>Projected</strong>: weather verified, a lineup still unconfirmed. <strong>Source unverified</strong>: a model row exists but its weather receipt is incomplete, so weather vectors are hidden. <strong>Incomplete</strong>: a required model input is missing. <strong>Roof</strong>: a closed or controlled venue, so outdoor wind is suspended.</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Posted total (over/under)</dt><dd>The market's line for combined runs in a game — e.g. 9.5. The instrument shows it as a reference beside its own weather read; it never posts a pick.</dd></div>
  <div><dt>Juice / vig</dt><dd>The margin books build into both sides of a total. Removing it (a "de-vig") turns the two prices into a clean probability — e.g. "over 52% / under 48%". Raw sportsbook prices are licensed and never displayed here; only this derived read is.</dd></div>
  <div><dt>The Market Read</dt><dd>How the instrument reacts to a posted total: it compares the direction of tonight's air (up or down versus the park's baseline) against the market's de-vigged lean — "pointing the same way", "opposite ways", or "the market is pricing something this instrument does not measure". A comparison, never advice.</dd></div>
</dl></div></section>

<section id="doctrine" class="method-section doctrine" tabindex="-1"><p class="section-number">06</p><div><p class="eyebrow">Public operating rule</p><h2>Honesty Is Part of the Instrument</h2><blockquote>Nothing unvalidated renders as validated. Missing weather does not become neutral weather. Thin evidence stays visibly thin. A model can inform a decision; it cannot make one safe.</blockquote><p>Market comparisons are informational, not wagering advice. If betting is legal where you live, you must be 21+ (or the legal age in your jurisdiction). Set limits, never chase losses, and use your local responsible-gaming resources if play stops being recreational.</p>
